00:00:00.320 --> 00:00:05.200
Researchers in Australia have created flexible
material with nanoscale glass structures that

00:00:05.200 --> 00:00:06.410
can manipulate light.

00:00:06.410 --> 00:00:11.580
A potential precursor to smart contact lenses
that display information.

00:00:11.580 --> 00:00:16.679
And RetroSense Therapeutics will inject viruses
loaded with the DNA of light-sensitive algae

00:00:16.679 --> 00:00:21.840
into the eye of a legally blind person in
the hopes of restoring their sight, in black

00:00:21.840 --> 00:00:23.160
and white.

00:00:23.160 --> 00:00:24.160
Vsauce!

00:00:24.160 --> 00:00:27.810
Kevin here - this is Mind Blow.

00:00:27.810 --> 00:00:33.580
This may be the most human-like robot hand
ever made.

00:00:33.580 --> 00:00:37.500
Researchers from the University of Washington
created the anthropomorphic robot hand by

00:00:37.500 --> 00:00:42.719
laser-scanning the bones of a human hand and
3D printing artificial replicas.

00:00:42.719 --> 00:00:45.710
And finally connecting them with artificial
finger joints.

00:00:45.710 --> 00:00:50.190
It’s controlled by 10 servos that act as
muscles with cable that replicates the carpal

00:00:50.190 --> 00:00:51.190
tunnel.

00:00:51.190 --> 00:00:55.370
And the hope is that someday this system could
be used as a scaffold for the growth of grafted

00:00:55.370 --> 00:00:59.000
cells to regenerate human hands.

00:00:59.000 --> 00:01:03.790
Tiny quartz discs could store data for billions
of years.

00:01:03.790 --> 00:01:08.660
First detailed in 2011, it stores data via
laser-etched nanostructures which can be read

00:01:08.660 --> 00:01:13.090
by passing light through the crystal and having
an automated microscope algorithm translate

00:01:13.090 --> 00:01:14.280
the light changes.

00:01:14.280 --> 00:01:18.930
The U.K. researchers now have a working prototype
and the next step is to speed up the write

00:01:18.930 --> 00:01:24.640
time as well as the read time of the discs
that can store 360 terabytes, can withstand

00:01:24.640 --> 00:01:31.040
temperatures up to 1,000 degrees and have
a room temperature lifespan of 13.8 Billion

00:01:31.040 --> 00:01:32.040
years.

00:01:32.040 --> 00:01:37.140
To free up traffic, Switzerland is considering
a special tunnel for automated delivery trucks.

00:01:37.140 --> 00:01:41.510
A three-lane tunnel, located 50 (164 feet)
meters underground would allow passage for

00:01:41.510 --> 00:01:43.630
the electric delivery vehicles.

00:01:43.630 --> 00:01:47.930
The idea is to completely eliminate big trucks
in urban areas and replace them with much

00:01:47.930 --> 00:01:51.920
smaller trucks that do the basic point A to
point B delivery.

00:01:51.920 --> 00:01:56.550
But first some private financing needs to
foot the $3.4 billion dollar bill and if that

00:01:56.550 --> 00:01:59.380
does happen - the earliest it would open is
2030.

